        'content'   => '<!-- wp:snel/content-section {"contentTranslations":{"en":["\\u003cp\\u003eI paid €200 per month for Beehiiv. For 4,000 subscribers. Just to send emails.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eNo fancy automations. No big campaigns. Just sending a newsletter to people who signed up via my blog or social media. €200 per month.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eAt some point, I thought: I’m a developer. I’ll build this myself.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003ch2 class=\\u0022wp-block-heading\\u0022\\u003eThe problem with Beehiiv, HubSpot, and Mailchimp\\u003c/h2\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eBeehiiv shows €43 per month on the homepage. Sounds reasonable. But as your list grows, the bill grows. With 4,000 to 5,000 subscribers, you quickly pay €200 to €300 per month.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eHubSpot starts at €9. Fine, you think. But as soon as you need segmentation or better automations, you go from €9 to €800 per month. For features that you don’t use 90% of the time.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eThis applies to all those tools. Mailchimp, ActiveCampaign, Klaviyo — they charge per subscriber. Your list grows, your bill grows. Most companies use only 10% of what such a platform offers. You just pay for the rest.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003ch2 class=\\u0022wp-block-heading\\u0022\\u003eWho I am\\u003c/h2\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eI’m Loc, a full-stack developer with over 10 years of experience. I build WordPress sites for businesses through Snelstack and use AI in my workflow — not as a replacement, but as an accelerator.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eI code practically every day. No course, no theory. Just building.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003ch2 class=\\u0022wp-block-heading\\u0022\\u003eWhat I’ve built\\u003c/h2\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eI built my own newsletter plugin for WordPress. It’s called Snel Newsletter.\\u003c/p\\u003e","\\u003cp\\u003eYou write an email like a regular blog post in the Gutenberg editor. The interface you already know. No new system 